<p>Just as with knowing how much money you‚Äôre able to invest in an outsourced project, you should also provide a specific timeframe the project needs to be developed and delivered within. This allows the developer to set expectations realistically. Be reasonable, though: if you‚Äôre one of those who answer ‚ÄúYesterday‚Äù when they‚Äôre asked when a deadline is, you won‚Äôt find remote developers and experts wanting to work with you. Forewarned is forearmed.</p>
<ol>
